# DispatchSEO self-hosted (docker compose) environment.
#   cp .env.docker.example .env
# Only CRON_SECRET is required - everything else has a sane default or is
# configured later in the dashboard's setup wizard.

# --- REQUIRED ---
# Auth token the cron container uses to trigger scheduled jobs. Generate:
#   openssl rand -hex 24
CRON_SECRET=

# --- Optional ---
# Password for the bundled Postgres. Only set this BEFORE the first boot -
# it is baked into the database volume at creation, and changing it later
# requires wiping the volume (docker compose down -v deletes all data).
# The default is fine for most setups: postgres is only reachable inside
# the compose network, never from the host or the internet.
# POSTGRES_PASSWORD=

# The URL your instance is reached at. start.sh fills this in for a local
# trial. With the bundled builder (CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN below) the whole
# pipeline runs in-stack and localhost is fine forever; only set a public
# URL if you skip the builder and rely on GitHub-hosted workflow schedules
# instead, which must be able to reach this URL.
# APP_URL=

# --- The in-stack builder (automatic content builds, no public URL) ---
# Your Claude Code OAuth token - the builder runs your agent headlessly on
# your existing Claude subscription (same BYO model as the cloud path). On
# your own machine run:
#   claude setup-token
# and paste the sk-ant-oat... token here, no line breaks. Without it the
# builder container idles and scheduled builds don't run.
# CLAUDE_CODE_OAUTH_TOKEN=

# GitHub access for the builder (clone, push, open + merge PRs). Normally
# NOT needed here: the builder reuses the token you connect in the setup
# wizard's One-tap merge step. Set this only to override it.
# BUILDER_GH_TOKEN=

# Host port the dashboard is published on (container always listens on
# 3000). Leave unset and start.sh picks 4005, or the next free port up if
# something already holds it. Set it to pin a specific port.
# DISPATCH_PORT=

# --- Optional overrides (the setup wizard handles all of these) ---
# DASHBOARD_PASSWORD=
# MCP_API_KEY=
# GSC_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=
# GSC_SITE_URL=
# DATAFORSEO_LOGIN=
# DATAFORSEO_PASSWORD=
# GH_MERGE_TOKEN=
# RESEND_API_KEY=
# ALERT_EMAIL=
# ALERT_EMAIL_FROM=
# SEED_KEYWORDS=

# Force building the app + builder images from this clone's source instead
# of pulling the prebuilt ones from GHCR. Set this if you forked the repo
# and changed code - otherwise start.sh prefers the prebuilt images when
# they're pullable, and your local changes would not run.
# BUILD_FROM_SOURCE=1
